author: CNN
description:
President Donald Trump — who blamed the shutdown in part yesterday for GOP losses — told Republicans they are getting “killed” politically by the impasse, a source said. But GOP leadership has downplayed the link between the shutdown and Democratic wins.

CNN anchor and chief Congressional correspondent Manu Raju reports from Capitol Hill and CNN's Boris Sanchez speaks with Rep. Don Bacon (R-NE). #CNN #News
title: Source: Trump told Republicans they're getting 'killed' on shutdown

author: CNN
description: In the most significant economic case to reach the Supreme Court in years, Trump’s authority to issue emergency tariffs faced deep skepticism from key conservatives — including Justices Amy Coney Barrett and Neil Gorsuch. But even still, CNN's Chief Supreme Court Analyst Joan Biskupic explains why the case may not be a slam dunk for the plaintiffs. #CNN #politics
title: Trump's tariffs go before Supreme Court

author: CNN
description: Faced with the prospect of armed conflict with the United States, Venezuela’s government seems to be encouraging citizens to spy on each other by using a revamped mobile application to report suspicious people or activities. VenApp, originally launched by President Nicolás Maduro in 2022, is being used as a tool for Venezuelans to inform the government of anything that it might consider seditious or disloyal. #cnn #news #venezuela #maduro
title: Venezuela urges residents to report neighbors with app

author: CNN
description: Prince William commends the climate change trailblazers involved in his environmental award, The Earthshot Prize, saying it is because of them that he tells his children they will have a brighter future. Speaking to CNN's Christiane Amanpour at the awards final in Rio de Janeiro in Brazil, he stressed the importance of telling kids there are "good things to come."  #CNN #News
title: Prince William tells his children they will have a brighter future thanks to climate change 'heroes'

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Pete Muntean breaks down the visual clues after a UPS cargo plane crashed shortly after taking off in Louisville, Kentucky. At least nine people have died and officials warn the death toll could climb as the investigation continues. #cnn #news

author: CNN
description: Under Israeli military escort, CNN's Jeremy Diamond visited an Israeli military position near the “yellow line” in Gaza City's Al-Shujaiya neighborhood. The “yellow line” separates Israeli-occupied Gaza from the remainder of the strip that Israel has withdrawn from. But with very few markers on the ground, it is difficult to distinguish the contours of that line. Multiple Palestinian civilians have been killed while crossing over the invisible line, as have suspected Hamas militants. The Israeli government continues to bar foreign journalists from independently entering Gaza.
title: The invisible line separating Gaza

author: CNN
description:
The death toll in the UPS plane crash in Louisville, currently at nine, is likely to rise, Kentucky Gov. Andy Beshear said late Wednesday morning. The governor added he believes members of the National Transportation Safety Board have arrived to begin investigating the Tuesday disaster.

Wolf Blitzer and Pamela Brown speak with CNN aviation safety analyst David Soucie and CNN correspondent Isabel Rosales reports from Louisville. #CNN #News
title: Update on deadly UPS crash investigation

author: CNN
description: At the Earthshot Prize in Brazil, CNN's Christiane Amanpour is backstage discussing her interview with Prince William about climate change and the upcoming COP30 climate summit also taking place in Brazil.

description: President Donald Trump’s attorney faced deep skepticism from several key conservative justices in early arguments at the Supreme Court over his sweeping global tariffs – a potentially troubling sign for the administration Chief Justice John Roberts and Justice Amy Coney Barrett, in particular, pressed the administration hard on several points, including whether the law at issue in the case authorized Trump to impose his emergency tariffs.  #CNN #News
title: Trump admin faces deep skepticism from Supreme Court on tariffs

description:
In the most significant economic case to reach the Supreme Court in years, the justices will weigh whether President Donald Trump acted lawfully when he imposed sweeping emergency tariffs against most trading partners. Those actions have been challenged by a group of small and medium-sized businesses, as well as a dozen states. 

CNN chief Supreme Court analyst Joan Biskupic previews the arguments, and CNN's Kate Bolduan speaks with former US Attorney Michael Moore. #CNN #News

author: CNN
description: Democrats scored major victories in the first election of President Trump’s second term, winning governorships in Virginia and New Jersey and electing Zohran Mamdani as New York City’s first Muslim mayor. The results highlight two rising models within the party: moderates like Abigail Spanberger and Mikie Sherrill, and progressives like Mamdani, a democratic socialist. With affordability and economic issues front and center, the wins give Democrats fresh momentum and a chance to redefine their path ahead of the 2026 midterms.
title: Democrats sweep key races in nationwide elections

author: CNN
description: Zohran Mamdani will be the next mayor of New York City. The Democratic socialist shocked the political establishment by beating former Governor Andrew Cuomo, first in the Democratic primary in June, and now after Cuomo ran as an Independent in the general election. At 34, Mamdani is the first Muslim and South Asian elected to the position and will become the youngest mayor in well over a hundred years to lead the biggest city in the US. #cnn, #news, #politics
title: Who is Zohran Mamdani?

description: Elon Musk loyalist Jared Isaacman is back as President Donald Trump's nominee to serve as administrator of NASA. Isaacman was previously tapped for the position before Trump unexpectedly withdrew his nomination earlier this year, citing a “thorough review of prior associations.” The reversal follows a behind-the-scenes feud with Transportation Secretary Sean Duffy, who has been leading the space agency in an interim position.
title: Musk ally Isaacman back in as Trump's pick for NASA administrator

description: California voters will approve Gov. #CNN #News

description:

description: Nearly 90% of Mamdani’s supporters say their vote is to support him, rather than to oppose his rivals. Sliwa’s voters also see their ballot as a statement of support, according to preliminary CNN exit polling findings. By contrast, Cuomo’s voters are closely split between voting to support him and voting to oppose the other candidates. #CNN #News
